messages.message:
Should we consider updating the table in the documentation since we do not support over ~800 pgs atm
cc: @Lee
@jean  Is this something we could change / document please?
Refering to this thread. Not sure if we want to discuss internally about this limitation https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0516UPPMT3/p1698947384142309?thread_ts=1698944606.083539&cid=C0516UPPMT3

@Lee, @joshbronko, absolutely! I want to clear this with product (cc @hannah) since that’s a change to the pricing doc, but we could change to “up to 800 pages” and remove the next line. Would you want to add a note about the limitation, or just drop pricing above 800 pgs?
Thanks! I think we need both in there until the limitation is removed, but i’ll let Hannah make the call

I think we should add in the limitation in the documentation for sure. As for changing the pricing table - going to flag this to @Varun Jain @Bastiane - who are working to do a refresh of the pricing table more broadly and consolidate the tiers. Maybe we can address this as part of that refresh?
Yes, will work with @Varun Jain to come up with an updated version soon!
